UGHELLI – The Delta State Ministry of Environment in collaboration with the Federal Ministry of Environment has distributed National Clean Cook Stoves to women in the State in a bid to mitigate greenhouse gas emission. The Permanent Secretary in the Ministry, Mr. Pius Anuku while distributing the Clean Cook Stoves to women from across the 25 local government areas in Asaba stated that government desired to achieve a low emission development strategy for the state through her climate change adaptation and mitigation actions. According to the Permanent Secretary, “There is the need for a paradigm shift from cooking with the traditional tripod cooking stove to the improved clean cook stoves which use less firewood.